<h1>Quantum Mechanics and Postmodernism</h1>

<h2>The Role of the Individual</h2>

<p>So we cannot achieve a complete understanding of our universe because the universe is not deterministic. But perhaps the next most notable aspect of quantum mechanics is the role of the "observer."</p>

<h3>Wave-Particle Duality</h3>

<p>The notion of "wave-particle duality" is the idea that all particles behave as both a wave and a particle simultaneously. This was demonstrated by the famous "double slit experiment" shown below.</p>

