<p>This is similar to the previous examples of superimposed states of being, except the system "collapses" to a single reality once someone observes the system. That is, by observing a particle, a person forces it to exist in a certain state. Here this idea is explained by theoretical physicists Fred Alan Wolf and Amit Goswami</p>

